0x46810000CAD1:
Evaporative Emission Control system leak detected (Small Leak).

--Possible Causes--
 - Loose fuel filler cap.
 - Small vapor leaks at the plastic vacuum line connection to the Vapor Management Valve (VMV).
 - Small vapor leaks at the fuel vapor hose connections to the VMV, the Fuel Tank Pressure (FTP) sensor and the fuel vapor storage canister.
 - Small cuts or holes in evaporative emission system.
 - EVAP Canister leaking.
 - CV Solenoid partially open when commanded closed.
 - Aftermarket parts and accessories nonconforming to the EVAP system specifications.

Note: DTC P0442/P1442 indicates that a leak has been detected [As small as 0.040 inch (.10cm)] in the Evaporative Emission System. Please reference 1998 or later PCED diagnostics for this code.

Idle Air Control(IAC) System Malfunction.

--Possible Causes--
 - Open IAC signal.
 - IAC signal shorted to VPWR.
 - Open VPWR at IAC solenoid.
 - Air inlet plugged.
 - Damaged IAC valve assembly.
 - Damaged throttle body.
 - Damaged PCM.

Note: The Powertrain Control Module(PCM) tests the Idle Air Control(IAC) system during Self-Test by adjusting the IAC solenoid and monitoring RPM. The Diagnostic Trouble Code(DTC) is set when the PCM does not measure any change in RPM after the IAC solenoid is adjusted accordingly.
